From a7ad0faceae94194ab7a2d87155c8cf07034de7a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dong Chenchen <superdcc97@163.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 15:47:13 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 15/27] fork: publish new pid namespace child_reaper via
 cmpxchg

copy_process() sets pid_ns->child_reaper to the newly forked task when
it is the first process (PID 1) of a fresh pid namespace.  Today this
store is a plain assignment relying on tasklist_lock write-held by the
caller for both mutual exclusion and memory ordering.

Mutual exclusion is not actually required: the is_child_reaper() branch
can only fire once per pid namespace, because PID 1 is allocated
exactly once by alloc_pid() in a given namespace and no other fork
will ever observe is_child_reaper() as true for it.  Memory ordering,
however, is load-bearing: any subsequent reader of pid_ns->child_reaper
(for example find_child_reaper() from exit.c or zap_pid_ns_processes())
must observe a fully-initialized task_struct.

Replace the plain store with cmpxchg(NULL, p).  cmpxchg provides the
release-side publication barrier we need and, as a bonus, defends
against any future accidental caller slipping a second writer in via
is_child_reaper() -- the WARN_ON_ONCE on a non-NULL previous value
would fire loudly.

This removes one of the load-bearing reasons copy_process() must hold
tasklist_lock write across this region.  It is still held for other
reasons (children list, ptrace_init_task, ...); follow-up commits
peel those off one by one.

No functional change from a reader's point of view: find_child_reaper()
still observes pid_ns->child_reaper under tasklist_lock write (its own
re-assignment path is left alone here), so its load remains well
ordered with respect to any fork() that could publish a new reaper.

Signed-off-by: Dong Chenchen <superdcc97@163.com>
---
 kernel/fork.c | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/fork.c b/kernel/fork.c
index 5cd2c7ec2a71..2b23e8989841 100644
--- a/kernel/fork.c
+++ b/kernel/fork.c
@@ -2576,7 +2576,20 @@ __latent_entropy struct task_struct *copy_process(
 			init_task_pid(p, PIDTYPE_SID, task_session(current));
 
 			if (is_child_reaper(pid)) {
-				ns_of_pid(pid)->child_reaper = p;
+				/*
+				 * Publish @p as the new pid namespace's child
+				 * reaper with a single atomic store that also
+				 * acts as a release barrier for the
+				 * task_struct fields initialized above.  This
+				 * branch can only fire once per pid namespace
+				 * (PID 1 is allocated exactly once), so the
+				 * cmpxchg is a publication primitive, not
+				 * contention resolution.  Removing the plain
+				 * store lets fork() drop its dependency on
+				 * tasklist_lock for this particular write.
+				 */
+				WARN_ON_ONCE(cmpxchg(&ns_of_pid(pid)->child_reaper,
+						     NULL, p) != NULL);
 				p->signal->flags |= SIGNAL_UNKILLABLE;
 			}
 			p->signal->shared_pending.signal = delayed.signal;
